# TC-23a — Work Calendar / Pay Period Foundation

## Purpose

Establish the foundational operational calendar and pay-period framework used by:

- employee time tracking
- weekly timesheets
- overtime calculation
- leave workflows
- payroll preparation
- payroll exports/imports
- Team360 payroll visibility
- operational payroll reporting

TC-23a defines shared operational workforce-period semantics for employee payroll workflows before downstream Phase 5 implementation begins.

TC-23a intentionally remains lightweight and operational in scope. TeamCORE is not a payroll tax engine or accounting platform.

**Normative companion:** [ADR-0002 — Payroll period and workweek foundations](../../adr/adr-0002-payroll-period-and-workweek-foundations). **MVP time posture:** employee payroll-oriented time is **daily-hours-based**; **punch/timeclock** capture is **out of MVP** (see Excluded and Future-Compatible Areas).

---

# Scope

## Included

### Agency payroll/work-calendar configuration

- Payroll frequency (**one frequency per agency** in MVP)
- Workweek start day
- Agency payroll timezone (single timezone per agency in MVP)
- Weekly overtime threshold
- Pay-schedule anchor semantics for weekly/biweekly/monthly (semimonthly uses fixed halves)

### Payroll period management

- Automatic pay-period generation
- **Non-overlapping** pay periods within an agency
- Pay-period lifecycle (`open`, `closed`)
- Payroll-period summaries
- Payroll-period completeness validation
- Payroll export linkage/history

### Payroll earning vocabulary (foundation)

- Fixed system earning codes (e.g. `REG`, `OT`, `PTO`, `HOL`, `SICK`) and categories for downstream summaries and exports — catalog only in TC-23a; agency-configurable earning-code engines are deferred

### Overtime foundations

- Weekly overtime aggregation
- Workweek boundary semantics
- Worked-hours vs leave-hours distinction
- Continuous overtime visibility

### Payroll summary foundations

- Regular hours
- Overtime hours
- Leave hours
- Total paid hours

### Payroll closure workflows

- Closure validation
- Administrative override posture
- Capability-based closure authority

---

## Excluded

### Not implemented by TC-23a

- Employee time entry UX (see **MVP time-entry assumptions** below — TC-23a only defines calendar contracts)
- Timesheet approval workflows
- Leave approval workflows
- Payroll tax calculations
- Direct deposit
- Contractor settlement periods
- **Timeclock punch systems, biometric attendance, geofencing/GPS location tracking, attendance-enforcement engines**
- Scheduling engines
- Shift planning
- Payroll reconciliation engines
- Multi-timezone workforce handling
- Advanced overtime engines
- Retro payroll engines

